Head coach of Super Eagles, Gernot Rohr has released his starting XI to face Lesotho in today’s 2021 Africa Cup of Nations (AFCON) qualifier at the Setsoto Stadium. Rohr had already warned his players to stay humble when they tackle Lesotho on Sunday evening. Rohr’s men head to the game following a 2-1 victory over Benin Republic some few days ago. Below is Nigeria’s starting XI against Lesotho: Akpeyi, Awaziem, Ajayi, Troost-Ekong, Aina, Ndidi, Aribo, Iwobi, Chukwueze, Osimhen, Simon The kick-off time for the match is 5pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.